%I A395303 #8 Apr 20 2026 09:25:21
%S A395303 0,1,2,5,4,9,18,37,8,17,34,69,68,137,274,549,16,33,66,133,132,265,530,
%T A395303 1061,264,529,1058,2117,2116,4233,8466,16933,32,65,130,261,260,521,
%U A395303 1042,2085,520,1041,2082,4165,4164,8329,16658,33317,1040,2081,4162,8325
%N A395303 a(n) is the least k > 0 such that A162439(k) = n; a(0) = 0.
%C A395303 The binary expansion of a(n) is the concatenation of the binary expansions of the distinct powers of 2 (in decreasing order) summing to n.
%C A395303 A permutation of A333256.
%H A395303 Rémy Sigrist, <a href="/A395303/b395303.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 0..8192</a>
%H A395303 <a href="/index/Bi#binary">Index entries for sequences related to binary expansion of n</a>
%F A395303 A000120(a(n)) = A000120(n).
%F A395303 a(n) >= n with equality iff n = 0 or n is a power of 2.
%e A395303 The first terms, in decimal and in binary, are:
%e A395303   n   a(n)  bin(n)  bin(a(n))
%e A395303   --  ----  ------  ----------
%e A395303    0     0       0           0
%e A395303    1     1       1           1
%e A395303    2     2      10          10
%e A395303    3     5      11         101
%e A395303    4     4     100         100
%e A395303    5     9     101        1001
%e A395303    6    18     110       10010
%e A395303    7    37     111      100101
%e A395303    8     8    1000        1000
%e A395303    9    17    1001       10001
%e A395303   10    34    1010      100010
%e A395303   11    69    1011     1000101
%e A395303   12    68    1100     1000100
%e A395303   13   137    1101    10001001
%e A395303   14   274    1110   100010010
%e A395303   15   549    1111  1000100101
%e A395303   16    16   10000       10000
%o A395303 (PARI) a(n) = { my (v = 0, e); while (n, n -= 2^e = exponent(n); v = (2*v+1) * 2^e;); return (v); }
%Y A395303 Cf. A000120, A162439, A333256.
%K A395303 nonn,base,new
%O A395303 0,3
%A A395303 _Rémy Sigrist_, Apr 19 2026
